        "created_at": "2025-04-17T19:12:09.047Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I don’t know if I’m supposed to do this or I’m breaking some rules but since this post got no attention i wanted to add few nit-picks.<br>\nI have no idea why is the chat bubble <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/speech_balloon.png?v=12\" title=\":speech_balloon:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":speech_balloon:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">  on the left side for me the sender. It’s very counter intuitive and I can’t get used to it. If the language is RTL why is the <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/speech_balloon.png?v=12\" title=\":speech_balloon:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":speech_balloon:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> on the left side?<br>\nHopefully this post gets some traction because i like the app and i think it’s localization is top notch and these things i pointed to are little and very few but break the user experience.</p>",
